{
  "texts": [
    "SIAUI builds on SIA by assuming that the central server and the LLM server share a mutual interest in obtaining user 𝑢 𝑖 's interacted items, leading them to share their prior knowledge: the user's perturbed sequence S 𝑢 𝑖 and the user's uploaded model M 𝑟 +1 𝑢 𝑖.",
    "In detail, the attacker compares M 𝑟 +1 𝑢 𝑖 with M 𝑟 to infer a set of client 𝑢 𝑖 's trained items V 𝑡𝑟𝑎𝑖𝑛𝑒𝑑 𝑢 𝑖 by calculating the non-zero item embedding gradients.",
    "This trained set includes both interacted items and negative samples.",
    "Similar to SIA, for 𝑣 𝑢 𝑖 𝑡 ∈ S 𝑢 𝑖, SIAUI converts it into v 𝑢 𝑖 𝑙𝑙𝑚,𝑡.",
    "Then, SIAUI only needs to select the most similar items from the trained item set V 𝑡𝑟𝑎𝑖𝑛𝑒𝑑 𝑢 𝑖, which is much easier than SIA guesses from the whole item set.𝑣 𝑢 𝑖 𝑡 = 𝑎𝑟𝑔𝑚𝑎𝑥 𝑣 ∈ V 𝑡𝑟𝑎𝑖𝑛𝑒𝑑 𝑢 𝑖 𝑠𝑖𝑚(v 𝑙𝑙𝑚, v 𝑢 𝑖 𝑙𝑙𝑚,𝑡)(12)Algorithm 4 introduces SIAUI briefly with pseudo-code."
  ]
}